node.accessibility_caption: Photo by snoopdogg on August 01, 2021. May be an image of 4 people and people standing.
Photo by snoopdogg in Los Angeles, California. May be a black-and-white image of 1 person and text that says '× T nytimes'.

node.text:
Nearly 30 years after emerging as a rapper from Long Beach, California, Snoop Dogg has transcended his hip-hop roots and become culturally ubiquitous. He is in the new Addams Family movie, on a Corona commercial, has a show with Martha Stewart on VH1 and an investment fund — and is still releasing new music.
 
Zooming from his compound in Los Angeles, he smoked an enormous blunt while discussing how he went from a shy musician to a multiplatform entrepreneur with several new ventures in the burgeoning cannabis industry.
 
“Companies that get down with me know how I get down.” 

Tap the link in our bio for our full interview with @snoopdogg. Photo by @maggiehshannon. @nytimes
